question:
What will be the output of the following C code?

```c
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    char str[] = "Hello";
    printf("%s", str);
    return 0;
}
```

What does the following C code output?

```c
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    char str[] = {'H', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o', '\0'};
    printf("%s", str);
    return 0;
}
```

What is the length of the string in the following C code?

```c
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    char str[] = "Hello\0World";
    printf("%lu", sizeof(str)/sizeof(str[0]));
    return 0;
}
```

What will be the output of the following C code?

```c
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    char *str = "Hello";
    str[0] = 'h';
    printf("%s", str);
    return 0;
}
```

What is the output of the following C code?

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
int main() {
    char str1[] = "Hello";
    char str2[] = "World";
    strcat(str1, str2);
    printf("%s", str1);
    return 0;
}
```
